{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "06", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "13", "M": "04", "S": "02"}}, "news": [{"title": "Delhi HC impleads JK Paper as defendant in the legal dispute over Prithviraj Road bungalow", "para": "JK Paper Ltd is now a defendant in a Delhi High Court case. The dispute concerns a bungalow on Prithviraj Road. Punit Beriwala claims he made an advance payment for the property in 2004. JK Paper acquired the bungalow in December 2021 for Rs 250 crore. Beriwala's counsel informed JK Paper about his client's claim.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/delhi-high-court-adds-jk-paper-to-dispute-over-prithviraj-road-bungalow/131548522?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-48970/131548522.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Truhome Finance, Veegaland Developers get Sebi nod for IPO", "para": "Truhome Finance's proposed IPO comprises a fresh issue of equity shares worth Rs 1,500 crore and an offer-for-sale (OFS) aggregating to Rs 1,500 crore by promoter Mango Crest Investment. Veegaland Developers, a part of the V-Guard Group, plans to raise Rs 250 crore through an entirely fresh issue of shares. There is no OFS component in the proposed issue.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/truhome-finance-and-veegaland-developers-secures-ipo-approval-from-sebi/131544103?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-98744/131544103.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Delhi government to invoke DMA Act, empower DMs to act against unauthorised construction", "para": "Delhi government will recover losses from corrupt officials and invoke the Disaster Management Act 2005 following a fatal hotel fire. Chief Minister Rekha Gupta announced that negligent officials will face